Peru Stocks: Candente Advances; Buenaventura, Minera IRL Fall

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-06-24T17:26:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/peru-stocks-candente-advances-buenaventura-minera-irl-fall.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:56 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose 0.3 percent to 19,061.09. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index retreated 0.3 percent to 2,459.04.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)   gained as copper rose in New
York after a bigger-than-expected rise in orders for U.S.
durable goods revived prospects for manufacturing and metals
demand. The Canadian mining exploration company with operations
in Peru rose for the second time in eight days, advancing 4
percent to $1.30.  Gold producers dropped as a pledge by European Union
leaders to stabilize the region’s economy cut demand for gold as
a haven.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 1 percent to $37.22.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, declined 2.8 percent to $1.03.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver and
zinc producer, slid 0.5 percent to 38 soles as prices for the
metals declined.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
